    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks, that's a good start. Could you make it sound a bit less \"template\" though? Specifically, maybe add a sentence or two acknowledging how tough it is to make these decisions when you've met such high-quality candidates, just so it feels a little more human and less like a standard HR form.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a revised version:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the Senior Developer position at our Austin office. We were truly impressed by your technical skills and the passion you brought to our final interview. Unfortunately, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our specific cloud architecture needs.\n\nI want to start by saying how much we appreciated the time you took to meet with us, and how much we enjoyed getting to know you as a candidate. It's never easy to make decisions like this, especially when you're faced with candidates who are as talented and impressive as you are. But sometimes, the right fit is about more than just technical skills – it's about finding someone who can mesh with our team's unique culture and dynamics. In this case, we felt that the other candidate was the best fit for our organization.\n\nPlease know that this decision is final, and we appreciate the effort you invested in our hiring process. We were delighted to have you as a finalist, and we're grateful for the opportunity to have met you. We wish you the very best in your future endeavors and hope our paths will cross again soon.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nI",
